      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>garlic</strong> roughly and peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Break your <strong>cardamom pod[s]</strong> open and discard the outer green shell</p><p>Grind the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>cardamom seeds</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>black pepper</strong> (freshly ground is best!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> - this is your <strong>spice paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1527.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
